refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolcurl_setopt_array resourcech arrayoptions
Sets multiple options for a CURL session. This function is useful for setting a large amount of CURL options without repetitively calling curl_setopt.

  &reftitle.examples;




     Initializing a new CURL session and fetching a webpage



<?php
// create a new CURL resource
$ch = curl_init();

// set URL and other appropriate options
$options = array(CURLOPT_URL => 'http://www.example.com/',
                 CURLOPT_HEADER => false
                );

curl_setopt_array($ch, $options);

// grab URL and pass it to the browser
curl_exec($ch);

// close CURL resource, and free up system resources
curl_close($ch);
?>
